se}}</ref>\n\n== Remembrance ==\nHis influence and popularity during his life led to many children of the early 19th century, especially on the [[American frontier]], to be named after him.<ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=z_wTAAAAYAAJ&pg=PA412#v=onepage&q&f=false \"Clermont County\"] ''Historical Collections of Ohio: An Encyclopedia of the State. Volume 1.'' Columbus: H. Howe & Son, 1889, pp.&nbsp;412\u2013413, 418. Page 418 contains an engraving of an 1821 portrait of Dow, and a drawing of Dow preaching in New Haven, Connecticut in 1832.</ref> In the 1818 Washington almanac, there is a humorous anecdote about Lorenzo Dow saving a woman's infidelity by pretending to raise the devil (the woman's paramour, who was hiding in a barrel, which Dow set on fire).<ref>[http://www.worldcat.org/title/washington-almanac-for-the-year-of-our-lord-1818/oclc/15440901&referer=brief_results ''The Washington Almanac for the year of our Lord 1818 ...\"] Sharp, J. (1817). The Washington almanac, for the year of our Lord 1818. Baltimore [Md.]: Cushing & Jewett.</ref> His autobiography became a bestseller and the [[1850 U.S. Census]] counts Lorenzo as one of the most popular first names in America.<ref>Micklethwait, John, and Adrian Wooldridge. [https://books.google.com/books?id=jlNOHAr46HEC&pg=PA69&lpg=PA69&dq=lorenzo+name+popularity+1850+census&source=bl&ots=hBcynanRal&sig=8Y6PAM8sf1l07Rq2OdU3JUywWhE&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwiKxZTE4K3LAhVMOT4KHTi9AAAQ6AEIKTAD#v=onepage&q&f=false ''God Is Back: How the Global Revival of Faith Is Changing the World.''] New York: Penguin Press, 2009, p. 69-70.</ref>\n\n== Family ==\nHis wife, Peggy Dow (1780\u20131820), was almost as eccentric as her husband.<ref>Gilbert, Jesse S. [https://books.google.com/books?id=Lb8QAAAAIAAJ&lpg=PA411&ots=jRC6C84bst&dq=Peggy%20Dow%20eccentric&pg=PA411#v=onepage&q&f=false Lorenzo and Peggy Dow], ''Methodist Magazine and Review,'' Volume 59.</ref> She published her journal, entitled ''Vicissitudes in the Wilderness'' (1833).<ref>Dow, Peggy. ''Vicissitudes in the Wilderness: Exemplified in the Journal of Peggy Dow.'' Norwich, Conn: Printed by W. Faulkner, 1833.</ref>\n\n== Selected works ==\n* ''Polemical Works'' (1814)\n* ''The Stranger in Charleston, or the Trial and Confession of Lorenzo Dow'' (1822)\n* ''A Short Account of a Long Travel; with Beauties of Wesley'' (1823)\n* ''History of a Cosmopolite; or the Four Volumes of the Rev. Lorenzo Dow's Journal, concentrated in One, containing his Experience and Travels from Childhood to 1814'' (1814; many later editions); this volume also contains \"All the Polemical Works of Lorenzo.\" The edition of 1854 was entitled ''The Dealings of God, Man, and the Devil as exemplified in the Life, Experience and Travels of Lorenzo Dow''.,<ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=fz4XAAAAYAAJ ''History of a Cosmopolite, 1814 1st edn.'']</ref><ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=SYNllIx56rUC ''History of a Cosmopolite, 1848 5th edn.'']</ref><ref>[https://archive.org/details/historyofcosmopo00dowuoft ''History of a Cosmopolite, 1858 edn.'']</ref>\n\n== Notes ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== References ==\n* {{Appletons'|title=Dow, Lorenzo |volume=2 |year=1888|page=218 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=o6coAAAAYAAJ&pg=PA218}}\n* {{NIE|wstitle=Dow, Lorenzo}}\n* {{EB1911|wstitle=Dow, Lorenzo}}\n\n== Further reading ==\n*Dow, Lorenzo. [https://archive.org/stream/eccentricpreacher00dowl#page/n7/mode/2up ''The Eccentric Preacher: Or, a Sketch of the Life of the Celebrated Lorenzo Dow, Abridged from His Journal; and Containing the Most Interesting Facts in His Experience.''] Lowell: E.A. Rice & Co, 1841.\n*Dow, Peggy. [https://archive.org/stream/vicissitudesinwi00dowp#page/n5/mode/2up ''Vicissitudes in the Wilderness: Exemplified in the Journal of Peggy Dow.''] Norwich, Conn: Printed by W. Faulkner, 1833.\n\n== External links ==\n*{{Internet Archive author|sname=Dow, Lorenzo}}\n* Montgomery, Sue. [http://www.dentongenealogy.org/Lorenzo%20Dow.htm Lorenzo Dow